<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Cali on 04-26-2001 10:07 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">What ever happened to respect? Respect for others? For the other human being, just like YOU on the other side of the pixels?

I think that is what Georgia was getting to in the article.

When do we lose that respect? Because we are anonymous? We don’t have to go into work the next morning and see the faces of those we disrespected the night before?
Maybe because we feel we are stronger then them?  But what about tomorrow? When they are stronger then us? 

I am by no means uber.  I try very hard to be kind, honorable, generous and fair.  Just like I do in REAL LIFE.  

For people who do uber things (great examples Nuelaan) and enjoy doing it? Great! More power to you.
Sometimes the little people want to try the uber things too. Those ubers that rush over them (Camping Ragefire / Preping for VS, Trak whatever) are taking away others attempt to do the same fun things, get that rush you all so dearly love.  Let them try, so what if they fail! Then you will have your chance.  

No one person has the right to say "I am more important and my needs matter more then yours do, so we are taking this first."  No ONE.  We are all the same.  All of our "needs" matter just as much as the next persons.  I respect your right to exist and you respect mine.  Cooperation, consideration and respect go a long way.

Please don’t disrespect me, call me names simply because we play differently.  Blue servers vs. Red servers? Why? Both have people behind the pixels playing, so what if they play differently.  Don’t call me a "Carebear" simply because my play style isn't your play style.  I have never done anything to hurt you or stop you from playing your way, don’t disrespect me because we are different.  That’s called prejudice. 

Morality
Morals
The ability to tell right from wrong.

Is there a clear cut "Right" and "Wrong" here? Not really, no, I don’t think so.  But your entitlement to whatever you deem 'right' only extends as far as you.  It does not overlap or overshadow my entitlement to my own "right"

Just because we are different doesn’t make us enemies.


------------------
~Calimayrn Anam'Cara
50th Cleric of Tunare
~Calizana Rhinelander
Floating Barbarian Champion
[URL=http://www.lostorder.com]Lost Order of Akalabeth[/URL]
Veeshan</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
